ce  andrew’s father and grandfather eventually owned more than  medallions when they decided to sell some in the s no banks would provide the financing so that is when they got into the lending business banks would not lend to immigrants because they considered them too risky they did not understand the character of the immigrant and were not aware of the value and security of a taxi medallion medallion has since lent over  billion to the taxi industry but has chargedoff at least  million in medallion loans in  aloneaccording to regulatory filings regulators required medallion bank to take additional loan loss reserves for the quarter ended september   after a recent examination after increasing reserves medallion bank was undercapitalized in  the mursteins founded a familyowned company called medallion funding corp to build a taxi medallion lending business medallion funding earned returns on investment over  percent per year more recently medallion funding corp and its subsidiaries were sued in a new york court for failure to repay  million borrowed to finance chicago medallions that are currently underwater as recently as march  senior notes issued by medallion financial traded for just  of par value a level that is indicative of severe financial distress later life and careeredit andrew murstein after completing his studies at tufts university and new york university spent several years on wall street including a stop at salomon brothers where he learned the power of equity in funding a business he joined medallion funding fulltime in  and eventually took the company public in  murstein successfully launched medallion financial corp established to be the parent company of medallion funding as a public company trading on the nasdaq under the symbol mfin the company has financed the purchase of thousands more in newark cambridge philadelphia chicago boston and new york city is an established industry leader but taxi loans are only a part of the story the company also established or bought successful businesses that lend to a variety of small businesses such as dry cleaners convenience stores manufacturers distributors and later public companies in  murstein invested million to create a subsidiary which sold advertising on the tops of taxis the subsidiary eventually named medallion taxi media was enhanced in  with the acquisition of see level advertising murstein sold medallion taxi media to clear channel yielding  million in  about this time medallion financial corp set up its own bank medallion bank to fund many of the company’s endeavors due to aggressive lending and outsize losses the bank accepted tarp money in  the banks loan losses in  were worse than  of banks in its peer group according to the ffiec in  it accepted an investment from the us treasury a security it has yet to repay the bank currently pays a  aftertax dividend on this preferred security in  murstein with former baseball star hank aaron and former new york governor mario cuomo both medallion financial board members and former football star and congressman jack kemp now deceased formed a specialpurpose acquisition company spac which raised million to buy a professional sports team the spac reportedly bid for the chicago cubs and other sports properties but ended up not making a purchase because none of the properties the company evaluated had the right mix of profit potential and risk avoidance later that same year murstein organized and filed publicly a spac focused on the security industry and assembled a board of directors that included former fbi director louis freeh and initial head of homeland security and former pennsylvania governor tom ridge on november   medallion financial corp as part of an investment group which includes richard petty and douglas g bergeron signed and closed sale on racing assets of one of nascars great names richard petty motorsports medallion is the largest owner of the team in  along with partners richard mack and nfl lege