urstein with former baseball star hank aaron and former new york governor mario cuomo both medallion financial board members and former football star and congressman jack kemp now deceased formed a specialpurpose acquisition company spac which raised million to buy a professional sports team the spac reportedly bid for the chicago cubs and other sports properties but ended up not making a purchase because none of the properties the company evaluated had the right mix of profit potential and risk avoidance later that same year murstein organized and filed publicly a spac focused on the security industry and assembled a board of directors that included former fbi director louis freeh and initial head of homeland security and former pennsylvania governor tom ridge on november   medallion financial corp as part of an investment group which includes richard petty and douglas g bergeron signed and closed sale on racing assets of one of nascars great names richard petty motorsports medallion is the largest owner of the team in  along with partners richard mack and nfl legend jim brown murstein acquired the long island lizards of major league lacrosse and renamed the team the new york lizards the team plays at hofstra university on long island and won the mll championship for the third time in the financial success of richard petty motorsports is unknown the company does not pay cash interest to medallion financial opting to roll interest into the balance due murstein publicly stated that medallion may sell part of its motorsports stake in october  but by december  richard petty motorsports made the decision to downsize to one car from two for the next racing season under murstein’s leadership medallion today manages over  billion of investments the company has paid out over  in dividends to its shareholders since going public but suspended dividends in  due to losses from declining taxi medallion values in  murstein told barrons that the chances of such a dividend cut were slim to none since the article was published dividends have been cut twice the latest cut from  to per share to zero personaledit murstein is married to barbara lynn rudnick they have two children kimberly and matthew and live in new york city murstein an avid sports fan can frequently be seen at his table at the very exclusive raos restaurant where he frequently dines with academy award winner leonardo dicaprio and hank aaron or in the front row at madison square garden and yankee stadium often with other bold faced names murstein also reportedly threw his son an epic bar mitzvah reception in  with guests that included governor andrew cuomo hank aaron and a special hourlong performance by nicki minaj referencesedit  a b httpswwwnytimescomstyleandrewmursteinwedsmissrudnickhtml  a b forbes magazine online profile posted online  retrieved feb   httppeopleforbescomprofileandrewmmurstein  a b medallion financial corp reports  first quarter results and announces ticker symbol changes to mfin and mfinl medallion financial corp website may    andrew murstein salary and stock options for medallion financial corporation salarycom may   httpwwwsalarycomandrewmmursteinsalarybonusstockoptionsformedallionfinancialcorphtml  stock dividends longrundatacom retrieved    “andrew murstein president” medallion financial corp website retrieved may   wwwmedallioncomaboutseniormgmtmursteinhtm  andrew murstein et al the business of funding new york aspatore inc  p  a b “andrew murstein ” by peter grant “ under ” crain’s new york business jan  feb   p   a b c d medallion financial corp retrieved oct   website wwwmedallioncom  “nyc taxi medallions worth hailing” by taylor mcgraw usa today aug   p b  a b c d “so you want to go public” by stan luxenberg family business magazine winter  issue magazine  a b c “hailing new customers” by tania padgett newsday nov   pa magazine  “a lender hopes to profit from the new taxi math” by tim gray the new york times jan   httpwwwnytimescombusinessinvestin